# ACME Salary Platform — Core Rules

Read `docs/engineering-standards.md` and `docs/roadmap.md` before implementing features.

## Must follow

- **TDD:** Failing test first, then implementation. No untested business logic.
- **DI:** Services receive repository **interfaces** via constructor. Wire concretes only in `backend/src/container/`.
- **Layers:** routes (HTTP) → services (use cases) → repositories (DB) → domain (pure rules). No SQL in services; no business logic in routes.
- **Append-only:** `compensation_history` is insert-only. Repositories must not expose update/delete for history.
- **Currency:** Analytics and totals are per ISO currency — never blend currencies.
- **Shared contracts:** Types/enums in `@acme/shared`. Zod validates API I/O.

## Must not

- Skip tests or add them "later"
- Import Drizzle/SQL directly in services or routes
- Put business rules in Next.js components
- UPDATE/DELETE compensation history rows
- Generate dynamic SQL (especially for AI features)

## Done when

- Roadmap item tests pass, lint/typecheck pass, PRD rule covered by test
